INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '96e3cc89-c7f1-4640-a167-48abcd73e0f5',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$esbuild Monitoring — Build Time Tracking and Bundle Size Regression Alerts in CI$escape$,
  $escape$esbuild exposes bundle metadata through the `metafile` build option. Enable it and `result.metafile.outputs` maps every output file to its `bytes`, `inputs`, and full import graph — no extra plugin required. esbuild doesn't surface timing internally, so wrap `esbuild.build()` with `performance.now()` from Node's `perf_hooks`; since esbuild executes synchronously via its Go core, the measurement is clean with no async scheduling noise.

For CI regression gating, commit a `bundle-baseline.json` with your accepted `bytes` and `ms` thresholds. After each build, compute the delta: if `(newBytes - baseline.bytes) / baseline.bytes > 0.05`, fail the pipeline with `process.exit(1)`. Pipe `esbuild.analyzeMetafile(result.metafile)` output to a GitHub Actions step summary for PR-level visibility — it renders a tree showing exactly which inputs account for which byte counts.

Update the baseline file on main only for intentional size increases, keeping the diff reviewable. This gives you sub-second CI feedback without a separate Webpack Bundle Analyzer or third-party service.$escape$,
  $escape$import * as esbuild from 'esbuild';
import { readFileSync } from 'fs';
import { performance } from 'perf_hooks';

const baseline = JSON.parse(readFileSync('./bundle-baseline.json', 'utf8'));
const t0 = performance.now();
const result = await esbuild.build({
  entryPoints: ['src/index.ts'],
  bundle: true, outfile: 'dist/index.js', metafile: true,
});
const elapsed = performance.now() - t0;
const bytes = result.metafile.outputs['dist/index.js'].bytes;
if ((bytes - baseline.bytes) / baseline.bytes > 0.05) {
  console.error(`Size regression: ${bytes} vs ${baseline.bytes} bytes`); process.exit(1);
}
console.log(await esbuild.analyzeMetafile(result.metafile));$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
